            <thetext>Added a argument to getWheelDelta, which is a method already available on the mouse wheel event. Giving no argument will return the same data as before so nothing changed here.
Giving an axis as string (&quot;x&quot; or &quot;y&quot;) will return the mouse wheel delta vor the given axis. I used that information in all the frameworks usage of getWheelDelta to get the two dimensional scrolling for all widgets. This is especially useful for the abstract scroll area and the table.

